    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense enters today with **Gunnar Henderson** as our anchor, holding a standout score of 83.29. Facing Seth Lugo, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits significantly from a favorable wind forecast and a prime leadoff spot, effectively insulating his value despite the inherent risk of targeting an elite hold pitcher. **Andy Pages** (75.64) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) round out our top-tier plays, both capitalizing on favorable park factors and high-leverage platoon matchups against opposing starters Quintanta and Elder. **Drake Baldwin** also earns a strong recommendation at 72.11; his placement in the #2 hole against Jake Irvin is a primary driver, as the matchup against a sub-5.00 xERA arm provides the exact offensive environment we need to push for category gains.\n\nManaging our game caps remains a priority, leading to a difficult benching decision for **Nolan Schanuel**. While his 50.08 score was respectable, he was ultimately displaced by the higher defensive and situational utility of our primary starters. We are keeping a close watch on **Josh Lowe** (53.92), whose score is suppressed by the matchup against Dylan Cease; while he remains in the lineup to protect our stolen base potential, his proximity to the marginal threshold serves as a warning that we may need to pivot if early at-bats prove fruitless. We are also monitoring **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (57.76), whose production is slightly dampened by a matchup against Reid Detmers; despite a strong xwOBA, the SP skill delta forces us to temper expectations for the power-hitting corner infielder today.",
